          },
          "datePublished": "2023-07-31",
          "reviewRating": {
            "@type": "Rating",
            "ratingValue": "1",
            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "Horrible experience.\nIrresponsible behaviour, unprofessional staff, inconvenience unlimited..\n\nWe took early admission in Nov 2022. And the session did not start in April 2023 as per the previous communication. While the central team would call me asking why my kid is not attending the session, the local team had no clue when the session will begin. In June, when admissions were closed in all good prestigious schools, we are informed that Kharadi branch will not be working and kids were moved to other campus. We cancelled admission and were promised refund in 15days but it has been more than 1.5 months. Still entire amount is not refunded.",
          "publisher": {
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "Yellow Slate"
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Review",
          "itemReviewed": {
            "@type": "School",
            "name": "Orchids The International School - Kharadi"
          },
          "author": {
            "@type": "Person",
            "name": "Jaydeep Jadav"
          },
          "datePublished": "2023-07-27",
          "reviewRating": {
            "@type": "Rating",
            "ratingValue": "1",
            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "Over a period of two years, the school completely failed to address parents' concerns regarding building management, operations, finances, and refunds.\n\nPlease don't tell your family members or anybody else you know about this pitiful fake brand. Please spread the word about this information so that others are aware of it.\n\nI revoked my children's admission on June 16 due to the school's persistent management issues and their academic difficulties.\n\nSince then, I've been pursuing a refund, but no one has cared to get back to me. The school is enjoying our hard-earned money and playing us for fools.\n\nZero ethics. Seriously guys shame on you. Have some courtesy to provide the update to parents.",
          "publisher": {
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "Yellow Slate"
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Review",
          "itemReviewed": {
            "@type": "School",
            "name": "Orchids The International School - Kharadi"
          },
          "author": {
            "@type": "Person",
            "name": "Prasad DVS"
          },
          "datePublished": "2023-07-14",
          "reviewRating": {
            "@type": "Rating",
            "ratingValue": "1",
            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "Possibly I would have not rated or under-rated the school not for its academics wise, but for the worst communication and poor management. The school has fully failed to handle parents concerns over 2 years, with building management, operations, Financials and refunds. Due to the ongoing issues with school management and their academic problems, I withdrawn my kids admission on 10th Jun. Since then been following up for refund and no one cares to respond. If it was fee payment part from a parent, they even go to extend that they wont even give kids volume books, dont allow participation in activities etc.",
          "publisher": {
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "Yellow Slate"
          }
        }
